but there's never been a good way to

00:19:12.116 --> 00:19:18.659
differentiate an aleph and an ein in

00:19:19.159 --> 00:19:20.259
Hebrew transliterations.

00:19:21.118 --> 00:19:23.519
The old school was you had a forward

00:19:23.559 --> 00:19:25.319
or a backward single quotation mark,

00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:27.200
which would also be an apostrophe.

00:19:27.921 --> 00:19:29.320
On a closed quotation mark,

00:19:29.340 --> 00:19:30.161
it'd be an apostrophe.

00:19:30.941 --> 00:19:33.622
But the single quotation mark closed and

00:19:33.701 --> 00:19:36.481
open was the patented way of doing it.

00:19:36.642 --> 00:19:38.403
But no one ever knew what that stood

00:19:38.423 --> 00:19:38.643
for.

00:19:38.982 --> 00:19:40.403
So it didn't help anybody because they

00:19:40.423 --> 00:19:41.303
didn't know what it stood for.

00:19:41.363 --> 00:19:44.243
And then it doesn't work in Microsoft Word

00:19:44.263 --> 00:19:47.265
because Microsoft Word commandeers

00:19:47.805 --> 00:19:51.445
quotation marks and decides how they think

00:19:51.465 --> 00:19:52.465
you want to convey it.

00:19:52.885 --> 00:19:54.385
And there's so many different styles that

00:19:54.506 --> 00:19:55.346
it didn't work.

00:19:57.974 --> 00:20:00.957
I came up in conversations with Joe just

00:20:00.977 --> 00:20:03.138
the other day with a way that we

00:20:03.159 --> 00:20:04.839
could do it that no one's done it

00:20:04.859 --> 00:20:06.560
before because we've now come up with our

00:20:06.661 --> 00:20:11.163
own font by looking at the lead tablet

00:20:11.424 --> 00:20:14.227
found on Mount Ebel and looking at all

00:20:14.267 --> 00:20:15.607
of the variations of

00:20:16.521 --> 00:20:18.222
of what is that most ancient script,

00:20:18.304 --> 00:20:20.365
because some people call it Canaanite,

00:20:20.384 --> 00:20:21.685
some people call it Phoenician,

00:20:21.726 --> 00:20:23.268
some people call it Paleo-Hebrew,

00:20:23.948 --> 00:20:26.009
some call it Moabite stone.

00:20:26.049 --> 00:20:27.892
It has a hundred different names,

00:20:27.951 --> 00:20:30.933
but it's the original pictograph script.

00:20:31.515 --> 00:20:34.596
And so we looked at every nation around

00:20:34.636 --> 00:20:36.077
there, around the region,

00:20:36.578 --> 00:20:38.299
all of which have a variation of that

00:20:38.339 --> 00:20:38.661
script.

00:20:39.497 --> 00:20:42.439
And we looked at the earliest versions we

00:20:42.459 --> 00:20:42.960
could find,

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:44.921
what they were trying to say and how

00:20:44.961 --> 00:20:45.642
it was drawn.

00:20:46.001 --> 00:20:47.643
And so we actually created our own font.

00:20:47.663 --> 00:20:50.765
So that's another, by the way,

00:20:50.785 --> 00:20:52.507
and that's on the resources there.

